[2]
Date: Wed 13 Nov 2002
From: "Banks, A-Lan" <A-Lan.Banks@derwent.co.uk>
Source: The Herald (Glasgow), Wed 13 Nov 2002 [edited]
<http://www.theherald.co.uk/>

Scotland: outbreak of Norwalk-like virus infection in cancer hospital
---------------------------------------------------------------------
Cancer patients are the latest victims of the winter vomiting [disease
virus]. A ward at the Beatson Oncology Centre in Glasgow has been closed to
new admissions because of an outbreak of the virus infection. Eight
patients and 3 members of staff have shown symptoms of the illness, which
has struck hospitals throughout Scotland over the past few months. A
Beatson Centre spokesman said no-one was in any danger, and the 21 bed
ward, F3, would re-open when the infection had cleared. Emergency
admissions were being accommodated elsewhere in the centre, and normal
patient care was not affected, she added. She said it would be tomorrow "at
the earliest before we admit any more patients to the ward".
(byline: Alan MacDermid)
--
Banks, A-Lan
<A-Lan.Banks@derwent.co.uk>
