[3]
Date: Sat 16 Nov 2002
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: BBC News Online, Sat 16 Nov 2002 [edited]
<http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/uk_news/scotland/2483061.stm>

Scotland: viral gastroenteritis closes wards in 2 Lanarkshire hospitals
--------------------------------------------
Patients and staff at 2 hospitals in Scotland have been struck by a mystery
infection which has closed two wards. The 2 wards, both for elderly people,
one at Hairmyres Hospital and one at Wishaw General Hospital, both in
Lanarkshire, have been hit by a vomiting and diarrhea outbreak.
A spokesman for Lanarkshire Health Board said 9 patients and 2 members of
staff at Hairmyres Hospital and 8 patients and one member of staff at the
Wishaw hospital have been affected. One patient with the illness at
Hairmyres died on Fri 15 Nov 2002, but the spokesman said this was due to
"prior medical conditions". He said in both cases the infection control
team was notified, outbreak control meetings were held and the wards were
closed to admissions. "Infection control measures were put in place and
staff movement within the hospital was restricted," he said.
There are fears the infection could spread after 8 other staff members
working in various areas of the Hairmyres Hospital also reported symptoms.
The spokesman said: "The outbreak control team will continue to monitor the
position with a high degree of vigilance." "No patients are giving cause
for concern."
